  "summary": {
    "as": "Introduced in House",
    "asOf": "2021-12-14",
    "date": "2022-05-03T17:15:19Z",
    "text": "For the Parents Act\n\nThis bill conditions receipt of federal education funds on compliance with guidance issued by the Department of Education on (1) banning in public education the teaching of critical race theory and the usage of any teaching methodology or curriculum that promotes or causes a racial divide or lack of equality, and (2) requiring that all races be treated equally. Specifically, institutions of higher education must comply with the guidance and each state must certify that each public elementary and secondary school in the state complies with such guidance."
